adjectives.description: murksome (comparative more murksome, superlative most murksome)

entries.meaning: Suggestive or indicative of murk; darksome.
examples: So, when stern Winter in his frozen vest Enfolds fair Nature's charms, the vaporous air, Surcharged and dense, repels the solar beam ; No genial ray falls on the languid earth, But, struggling with the dun, deep, murksome haze, [...]
